'''Going out with a bang''' was a code phrase that was used by [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|T-65 X-wing starfighter]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] in [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]] so that they would not tip off the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|enemy]]. It meant that the pilot who had recited the code would ditch his or her [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] and let the [[Astromech droid/Legends|astromech droid]] take it on a suicide run. It was usually used only as a last resort. During the Battle of [[Eidolon Base]], [[Tycho Celchu/Legends|Tycho Celchu]] used this phrase when his X-wing was badly damaged by [[TIE/IN interceptor/Legends|TIE/IN interceptors]].

